args: Apologies, Elisanne, but may I ask you to\ngo into town and do some shopping for us?
What, right now? We've only just finished\nthe hunt.
Can it not wait until we return home?
I just remembered that we're out of bread\nfor dinner.
If we return to the Halidom and then go\nshopping, it will delay the evening meal.
In that case, we'll send a few people.
This was a hard-won battle, though.\nThe only uninjured ones are me and...
Yes, wonderful. However you want to do it.\nJust please get the bread.
Oh, and I apologize for allowing our stores\nto fall so low.
By way of said apology, feel free to pick\nup a treat for yourselves.
...Within budget, of course. I don't want\nyou coming back with a diamond-tip cane.
Not to worry. All right, Elly. Shall we?
H-hold on a moment! I don't feel right\ngoing into town dressed like...this.
Hey, good point. We're all used to seein'\nit by now, but the townsfolk ain't.
I see how that might give them a start.
No, you mustn't! Your protection is my\nsworn duty as a Paladyn!
...And yet, this outfit truly IS beyond\nthe pale.
Trapped between duty and modesty.\nIt's a difficult choice.
No it isn't! What choice has a knight but\nduty?
Petty shame will not sway me from my\nsworn task!
C-come along, Your Highness. The whole\npoint is to get dinner started on time.
...They are staring.\n...They are most DEFINITELY staring.
Are you going to be all right, Elly?
Y-yes, I'm fine. I'll just block it out\nand get this over with.
Oy, welcome! We got a fresh batch straight\noutta the oven!
Mmm, it smells delicious. Let's get what\nwe need and hurry back.
...Hmm? What's that decoration they have\non the counter?
That is known as a jack-o'-lantern,\nYour Highness.
We're preparin' for Halloween, see?\nWhole town throws a festival on the\nbig day, so it does!
That sounds great! I'd love to come see it.
Er, but are we not holding our own party\nat the Halidom?
Yes, but I don't see why one should rule\nout the other. Two parties means twice the\nfun, right?
Bwa ha ha! This guy gets it!
Here, take this, party man. On the house!\nHope to see ya at the festival!
Hope to see you there too, cutie.
I'll not be subjected to this man's\nlasciviousness! We are leaving!
Er, I dunno what that means, but hey,\nthanks for stoppin' by!
Oh, I don't think he was so far off the mark.
What? Nonsense! I'm far from what anyone\nwould call—
Evening, miss! We've got a trove of cute\naccessories fresh in today. Have a look!
Ooo, a pair of jack-o'-lantern earrings...
If you like them, why not pick them up?\nCleo said you could, remember?
Here's a tip, buddy: When buying a gift for\nyour girlfriend, tell her it's ALMOST as\npretty as she is!
Oh, you two aren't...? Oops! My mistake.
The young lady is dressed so fashionably,\nI just assumed the two of you were out on\na date or somesuch.
You are mistaken! I am a... We are not...\nHOW DARE YOU, MADAM!
*huff* *pant* Oh, I knew this outfit would\nmake me the object of mockery.
I don't think anyone has been mocking you.
I should think they all meant what they\nsaid sincerely. They were just paying\nyou a compliment.
What?! Impossible. That would mean all\nthe business of being cute and fashionable\nwas actually...
M-may I ask Your Highness's opinion\non the matter, then?
Er, that is to say...do you think I look cute\nin this?
Sorry, what was that? I couldn't hear you\nover that sudden gust of wind.
N-nothing! I did not say a word!\nLet's hurry back.
Er, but I thought you wanted to ask\nme something.
Not me! No questions here! Ha ha!\nHurry now, mustn't keep dinner waiting!
